-- Russia Recovers to Defeat Slovakia 3-2, Reach Final of Fed Cup
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-04-21T19:21:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-21/russia-recovers-to-defeat-slovakia-3-2-reach-final-of-fed-cup.html
Russia came back from 2-0 down to
beat Slovakia 3-2 and reach the final of tennis’s Fed Cup.  Ekaterina Makarova and Elena Vesnina clinched the win with
a 4-6, 6-3, 6-1 doubles victory over Dominika Cibulkova and
Daniela Hantuchova in Moscow.  Earlier,  Maria Kirilenko  beat Cibulkova 7-5, 6-1 and
Makarova defeated Hantuchova 6-3, 4-6, 6-4 to level the match at
2-2.  The other semifinal, in Palermo, was delayed until
tomorrow, because of rain, with Italy leading the Czech Republic
2-1. The Fed Cup is the top team competition in women’s tennis.  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 